history.content: Since you are currently in Data 8, you haven't completed the necessary prereqs yet. CalCentral enforces the prerequisites by checking whether you have a grade for that class, so you wouldn't be considered eligible until after the finals this semester.

children.subject: There is an appeals form on the FAQ part of the Data Science 100 website

Thank you for your quick response. I have reviewed the FAQ page just now, and it seems that before filling out the appeals form, we should first add ourselves to the waitlist for the course. However, the original poster has mentioned that the class is showing that it is full and is not allowing him to have a waitlist option. Will I be able to put myself on the waitlist for this course if I have not completed the prerequisites yet?

Yes, you should be. Not sure why the original poster was not able to add themselves to the waitlist. You basically have to attempt to enroll in the class and the system should automatically put you on the waitlist.
Make sure that while enrolling on CalCentral, you have the "Waitlist if Full" option selected before adding the class.

I was the original person to ask the question and I figured it out :) I stupidly didn't realize that we had to choose sections 999 and 999A. If you do that, even if you're taking data 8 right now it should let you enroll. Sorry for the confusion, but thank you all for your help!
